Duplicate Daily Product IDs

A warehouse automation system in Chennai stores the product IDs scanned during the first half of a shift in an array. For reporting purposes, the system must generate a new array where the same sequence of product IDs is repeated twice in the same order.

Given an integer array nums of length n, create an array ans of length 2n such that:

ans[i] = nums[i] for 0 <= i < n
ans[i + n] = nums[i] for 0 <= i < n
Your task is to build this duplicated array and print the result.

Input format :
The first line contains an integer n — the size of the array.
The second line contains n space-separated integers representing the array elements
Output format :
Print 2n space-separated integers representing the concatenated array.

Code constraints :
1 <= n <= 1000
1 <= nums[i] <= 1000

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
3
1 2 1
Output 1 :
1 2 1 1 2 1
Input 2 :
4
1 3 2 1
Output 2 :
1 3 2 1 1 3 2 1

Solution:



// You are using GCC
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main(){
    
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    
    vector<int>arr(n);
    
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        cin>>arr[i];
    }
    
    vector<int>ans(2*n,0);
    
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        ans[i] = arr[i];
        ans[n+i] = arr[i];
    }
    
    
    for(int i:ans){
        cout<<i<<" ";
    }
}
